&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step Into Leadership | 3–4 Days/Week | No Overnights&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you ready to take the next step in your veterinary career? Sploot Veterinary Care is redefining primary and urgent care, and we’re seeking a strong clinical leader to help drive that work in Denver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Clinic Medical Director, you’ll practice gold-standard medicine while leading and mentoring a high-performing medical team. You’ll have the autonomy to shape clinic culture, influence clinical standards, and contribute to the continued growth and success of our care model. If you’re a collaborative, forward-thinking leader who is passionate about modern veterinary medicine and building something meaningful, this role offers the opportunity to make a lasting impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes Sploot Different&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible 3–4 day workweek with 10–12 hour shifts + No overnights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly skilled nursing team + 3:1 Nurse to DVM ratio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balanced mix of urgent care and wellness cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong pre-visit triage so you walk into the exam room prepared&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You a Great Fit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DVM/VMD degree (licensed and in good standing in Colorado)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of clinical experience, with leadership or mentorship experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for team-building – You believe a great team makes great medicine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational &amp;amp; strategic skills – You’re comfortable making decisions and driving outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A visionary mindset – You’re excited about changing the status quo in veterinary care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus Points: experienced in and excited about surgeries and dentals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the Lead Veterinarian on the clinic floor, setting the standard for patient care across the Sploot network&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement protocols, oversee quality assurance, and ensure every patient gets top-tier care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor, train, and empower veterinarians and nurses to grow in their careers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a collaborative, supportive environment where both pets and people thrive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help Scale a Modern Veterinary Model – Influence how Sploot expands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Perks of the Pack&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$150,000–$180,000 base salary, shift and experience dependent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A competitive ProSal model with high production rate and no negative accrual&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sign-on and relocation bonus to make joining Sploot even easier&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unlimited CE + $2,000 annual travel reimbursement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Pet Benefits to make sure your furry friends are covered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;100% employer-paid medical insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(k) with 4% match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous PTO, and up to 12 weeks paid parental leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full coverage of licensing, liability, and professional memberships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sploot is an equal opportunity employer and practices continuous hiring in accordance with Colorado state law. We welcome applications year-round and are committed to building a diverse and inclusive team.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-Onsite&lt;/p&gt;

